{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.39",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 39 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:1",
      "text": "The wise man will seek out the wisdom of all the ancients, and will be occupied in the prophets.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:2",
      "text": "He will keep the sayings of renowned men, and will enter withal into the subtilties of parables.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:3",
      "text": "He will search out the hidden meanings of proverbs, and will be conversant in the secrets of parables.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:4",
      "text": "He shall serve among great men, and appear before the governor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:5",
      "text": "He shall pass into strange countries: for he shall try good and evil among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:6",
      "text": "He will give his heart to resort early to the Lord that made him, and he will pray in the sight of the most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:7",
      "text": "He will open his mouth in prayer, and will make supplication for his sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:8",
      "text": "For if it shall please the great Lord, he will fill him with the spirit of understanding:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:9",
      "text": "And he will pour forth the words of his wisdom as showers, and in his prayer he will confess to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:10",
      "text": "And he shall direct his counsel, and his knowledge, and in his secrets shall he meditate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:11",
      "text": "He shall shew forth the discipline he hath learned, and shall glory in the law of the covenant of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:12",
      "text": "Many shall praise his wisdom, and it shall never be forgotten.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:13",
      "text": "The memory of him shall not depart away, and his name shall be in request from generation to generation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:14",
      "text": "Nations shall declare his wisdom, and the church shall shew forth his praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:15",
      "text": "If he continue, he shall leave a name above a thousand: and if he rest, it shall be to his advantage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:16",
      "text": "I will yet meditate that I may declare: for I am filled as with a holy transport.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:17",
      "text": "By a voice he saith: Hear me, ye divine offspring, and bud forth as the rose planted by the brooks of waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:18",
      "text": "Give ye a sweet odour as frankincense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:19",
      "text": "Send forth flowers, as the lily, and yield a smell, and bring forth leaves in grace, and praise with canticles, and bless the Lord in his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:20",
      "text": "Magnify his name, and give glory to him with the voice of your lips, and with the canticles of your mouths, and with harps, and in praising him, you shall say in this manner:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:21",
      "text": "All the works of the Lord are exceeding good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:22",
      "text": "At his word the waters stood as a heap: and at the words of his mouth the receptacles of waters:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:23",
      "text": "For at his commandment favour is shewn, and there is no diminishing of his salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:24",
      "text": "The works of all flesh are before him, and there is nothing hid from his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:25",
      "text": "He seeth from eternity to eternity, and there is nothing wonderful before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:26",
      "text": "There is no saying: What is this, or what is that? for all things shall be sought in their time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:27",
      "text": "His blessing hath overflowed like a river.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:28",
      "text": "And as a flood hath watered the earth; so shall his wrath inherit the nations, that have not sought after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:29",
      "text": "Even as he turned the waters into a dry land, and the earth was made dry: and his ways were made plain for their journey: so to sinners they are stumblingblocks in his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:30",
      "text": "Good things were created for the good from the beginning, so for the wicked, good and evil things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:31",
      "text": "The principal things necessary for the life of men, are water, fire, and iron, salt, milk, and bread of flour, and honey, and the cluster of the grape, and oil, and clothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:32",
      "text": "All these things shall be for good to the holy, so to the sinners and the ungodly they shall be turned into evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:33",
      "text": "There are spirits that are created for vengeance, and in their fury they lay on grievous torments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:34",
      "text": "In the time of destruction they shall pour out their force: and they shall appease the wrath of him that made them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:35",
      "text": "Fire, hail, famine, and death, all these were created for vengeance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:36",
      "text": "The teeth of beasts, and scorpions, and serpents, and the sword taking vengeance upon the ungodly unto destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:37",
      "text": "In his commandments they shall feast, and they shall be ready upon earth when need is, and when their time is come they shall not transgress his word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:38",
      "text": "Therefore from the beginning I was resolved, and I have meditated, and thought on these things and left them in writing,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:39",
      "text": "All the works of the Lord are good, and he will furnish every work in due time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:40",
      "text": "It is not to be said: This is worse than that: for all shall be well approved in their time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.39.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 39:41",
      "text": "Now therefore with the whole heart and mouth praise ye him, and bless the name of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
